This paper is about salient object detection using convolutional neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also proposes a new architecture for the neural network, which involves designing new pooling-based modules, which could fall under artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the performance of the model, which could be considered a machine learning (cs.LG) problem. Additionally, the paper mentions the speed of the model, which could be related to neural networks and optimization (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses the implementation of the model, which could be related to multimedia (cs.MM).
